            "text": "Treating acne scars in Katy, TX, involves a variety of clinical and aesthetic options. Because different types of scars (icepick, boxcar, or rolling) require different approaches, most specialists recommend a combination of the following treatments.\n\n### **1. Top Treatment Options in Katy**\n*   **Microneedling & RF Microneedling:** This is one of the most popular treatments in the area for improving skin texture and reducing the depth of \"pitted\" scars. \n    *   **RF (Radiofrequency) Microneedling:** Adds heat to stimulate deeper collagen production.\n    *   **Clinics:** **Glow Up MD**, **Katy Wellness Center**, and **Clearstone Laser Hair Removal & Med Spa** are highly rated for these services.\n*   **Laser Skin Resurfacing:** For more significant scarring, fractional CO2 or non-ablative lasers (like Fraxel) are used to \"vaporize\" damaged skin layers and reveal smoother skin.\n    *   **Clinics:** **About Face & Body Medical Spa** (Smartxide DOT CO2 laser) and **Hibiscus Aesthetics & Wellness** (AviClear and NeoClear Aerolase).\n*   **Chemical Peels:** Medium-depth peels like the VI Peel or TCA peels are effective for surface-level scarring and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (dark spots).\n    *   **Clinics:** **H-Town Aesthetics** (VI Peel Purify) and **Enchanted Beauty Plastic Surgery** (TCA Peels).\n*   **Subcision & Dermal Fillers:** For \"rolling\" scars that are tethered to deeper tissue, subcision involves a specialist using a needle to break the fibrous bands under the skin. Dermal fillers (like Juvederm or Bellafill) can then be used to lift the depression.\n    *   **Clinics:** **AVIVA Dermatology** (Subcision specialist) and **Nikko Dermatology** (Scar revision and fillers).\n\n### **2. Recommended Providers by Category**\nIf you are looking for medical-grade treatment, it is best to consult with a board-certified dermatologist or a medical spa supervised by a physician.\n\n| **Provider Type** | **Recommended Clinic** | **Specialty** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Medical Dermatology** | **Cinco Ranch Dermatology** | Comprehensive skin care and medical-grade scar assessments. |\n| **Cosmetic Specialist** | **Dermatology Associates of Katy** | Dr. Uyen Ngoc Mui offers targeted acne and scar treatments. |\n| **Advanced Med Spa** | **Hibiscus Aesthetics & Wellness** | Known for high-tech lasers like AviClear and personalized plans. |\n| **Aesthetic Surgery** | **About Face & Body** | Specializes in laser resurfacing and RF microneedling. |\n\n### **3. Estimated Pricing in Katy**\nWhile prices vary based on the number of sessions needed, here are typical local ranges:\n*   **Traditional Microneedling:** $300 – $450 per session.\n*   **VI Chemical Peels:** $200 – $300 per session.\n*   **Dermal Fillers:** $550 – $800 per syringe.\n*   **Laser Resurfacing:** $500 – $1,500+ depending on the intensity and area covered.\n\n### **4. How to Choose a Provider**\n1.  **Identify Your Scar Type:** Icepick scars often need **TCA Cross** or **punch excision**, while rolling scars need **subcision**. Ask the provider which specific scars they are targeting.\n2.  **Request a Consultation:** Most Katy clinics, such as **SkinSpirit** or **ViATA Aesthetics**, offer consultations to create a custom plan. \n3.  **Check Credentials:** Look for \"Board-Certified Dermatologist\" or \"Licensed Aesthetician\" to ensure the person operating lasers or needles has the proper medical training.",
